Package seng202.group2.view.graphs

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BooleanGraphOption.StateChangeListener
    A simple functional interface stub to facilitate use of lambda expressions for method addChangeListener.
    Plottable
    A basic interface used to specify a graph is intended to be user-visible.
    SelectionGraphOption.StateChangeListener
    A simple functional interface stub to facilitate use of lambda expressions for method addChangeListener.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BarGraph
    A Graph class that generates a Bar chart, plotting either two DataCategory subtypes against each other, or a single DataCategory subtype against the count of crime records which take on each value for that DataCategory.
    BooleanGraphOption
    A graph option which can either be enabled, or disabled.
    CrimesOverTimeGraph
    A TimeSeriesGraph type used to plot a graph of number of crime records over time.
    Graph
    A superclass specifying all methods which a Graph type must implement in order to interface with control classes.
    GraphConfigurationDialogController
    A controller for a dialogue box which is shown when graph options are not in a valid configuration for plotting.
    GraphOption
    A simple class used to interface setting graphing options between a Graph subtype and the parent class Graph.
    LineGraph
    A simple Graph type used to plot a line chart.
    NumericGraphOption
    A GraphOption used for getting a number from the user.
    ScatterGraph
    A simple Graph type used to plot a scatter chart.
    SelectionGraphOption<T>
    A GraphOption used for displaying a list of choices to the user, out of which the user chooses one.
    TimeSeriesGraph
    A LineGraph type which is used to plot a graph over time.
